Exercise 02 — GDB Variables
==============================

The program checks whether a local variable 'key' equals 0x1337.
It is initialized to 0 and never changed in the source code.

Your goal: use GDB to change 'key' to 0x1337 before the check runs.

  Load and break at main:
    gdb ./target
    break main
    run

  Step through until key is in scope, then inspect it:
    next
    print key

  Change it:
    set variable key = 0x1337

  Continue execution:
    continue

Change the key to reveal the flag, then submit it: horizon done HRZ{...}
